{
    "abstract": "The Segment Routing (SR) architecture allows a flexible definition of the end-to-end path by encoding it as a sequence of topological elements called \"segments\".  It can be implemented over the MPLS or the IPv6 data plane.  This document describes the IS-IS extensions required to support SR over the IPv6 data plane.  This document updates RFC 7370 by modifying an existing registry. ",
